---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { leagues } from "../data/leagues/index";
import { leagueSources, siteReviewDate } from "../data/sources";
---

<Base
  title="Data Methodology & Sources"
  description="How Last Season scopes, checks, sources and corrects historical football data."
  canonical="/methodology/"
>
  <div class="container">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><span class="current">Methodology</span></nav>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <h1>Data methodology & sources</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Clear scope, automated checks and an open correction process.</p>
    </section>
    <article class="prose section">
      <p class="callout"><strong>Current status:</strong> the archive structure and automated checks were reviewed on {siteReviewDate}. Manual primary-source review is continuing league by league.</p>
      <h2>Publication process</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>A season remains outside public derived totals until it is explicitly added to the published league configuration.</li>
        <li>Build-time checks test route metadata, duplicate positions, match totals, goal difference, champion consistency, total goals and top-scorer consistency.</li>
        <li>Pages identify when records are partial, illustrative or under review.</li>
        <li>Corrections are applied to the shared season record so connected club, player and comparison pages update together.</li>
      </ol>
      <h2>Definitions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Champion:</strong> the competition winner, which may differ from first place in competitions with playoffs.</li>
        <li><strong>Archive total:</strong> a total calculated only from published seasons represented on Last Season.</li>
        <li><strong>Top scorer:</strong> league goals in the named season unless the page states otherwise.</li>
        <li><strong>Kit colour study:</strong> a stylised representation of broad colours and era metadata, not a replica or authentication record.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Current results and fixtures</h2>
      <p>The match centre is deliberately separate from the reviewed historical archive. Recent results and upcoming fixtures are supplied by <a href="https://www.thesportsdb.com/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">TheSportsDB</a>, normalised by our Cloudflare Worker and cached briefly for performance. Current-feed records do not alter completed-season archive data.</p>
      <h2>Primary competition sources</h2>
      {leagues.map((league) => (
        <section>
          <h3>{league.name}</h3>
          <ul>
            {(leagueSources[league.slug] ?? []).map((source) => (
              <li><a href={source.url} rel="noopener" target="_blank">{source.name}</a> - {source.scope}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </section>
      ))}
      <h2>Corrections</h2>
      <p>Include the page URL, the field you believe is wrong and a primary-source link where possible. See the <a href="/corrections/">corrections page</a>.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>
